Similarly, abortion is only viewed as a necessary evil when appropriate circumstances exist, that is, rape and/or instances of saving the woman’s health (RE: cancer and other illnesses). The commonly perpetuated myth surrounding the idea of a female having to undergo a cesarean birth in order to save her life is that if one were to become stressed, especially in labour, she would then lose her life. In my rendering, this accentuates notions of gender as the female body is seen to be especially delicate, especially in pregnancy and labour. It is the duty of the male partner to guard and protect his female partner during this time. Similarly, if the woman’s life were to be endangered by an abortion, then it would further call into question both the biological ability and proven ability of the female to reproduce.
